lead_paragraph: Angelique Kerber suffered her first defeat as world number one when Petra Kvitova beat her 6-7(10) 7-5 6-4 in a marathon third- round match at the Wuhan Open in China on Wednesday.

headline.print_headline: World Number One Kerber Knocked Out by Kvitova in Wuhan
headline.main: World Number One Kerber Knocked Out by Kvitova in Wuhan
